olive oil
1 avocado
1 packet Plum Sauce
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet plant-based mince

• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook plant-based mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,
4-5 minutes.
• Add plum sauce and a splash of water and cook until slightly reduced,
1 minute.

• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts,
until warmed through.
• In a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of
rice wine vinegar and olive oil.

• Top tortillas with slaw, plum-glazed mince and avocado.
• Drizzle over plant-based mayo and top with crispy shallots. Enjoy!